Debouncing delays a function's execution until a specified time has passed since its last call, useful for limiting frequent events like window resizing or search input.

```javascript
function debounce(func, delay) {
  let timeoutId;
  return function (...args) {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => func.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}

// Example: Log a message only after the user stops typing for 300ms
const input = document.getElementById('search');
input.addEventListener('input', debounce((event) => {
  console.log('Searching for:', event.target.value);
}, 300));
```
